      "body" : "You can use any version of berkelydb with bitcoind, I always build with a newer version and have never seen any issues because of it.\r\nThe only reason that you have to provide `--with-incompable-bdb` (which is badly named) is that it will not be compatible with the stock bitcoin.org executables *as-is* (it's still possible to backport the wallet with `bdb_dump5.1 wallet.dat | bdb_import4.8` or such...).",
